author: Jeffery Martin
title: Washington Sheriff Refuses to Enforce Governor's Stay-at-Home Order, Says He's 'Worried About the Economy'
description: "The impacts of COVID 19 no longer warrant the suspension of our constitutional rights," Sheriff Fortney wrote Tuesday.
content:
Sheriff Adam Fortney of Snohomish County in Washington State wrote in a Tuesday Facebook post that he would not be enforcing the stay-at-home orders enacted by Washington Governor Jay Inslee.
